## Build

1. `herdr-turn-ping/index.ts` — default-export factory, target the installed pi 0.80.6 API (`~/.local/share/fnm/aliases/default/lib/node_modules/@earendil-works/pi-coding-agent/dist/core/extensions/types.d.ts`). Pane id from `process.env.HERDR_PANE_ID`, fallback `herdr pane current` (exec once at startup, cached); if neither resolves, register nothing / emit nothing. Await appends; serialize via a promise chain; catch and swallow (log via pi's notify at most once) append failures — the extension must never break a worker.
